          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2228Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the bulgur wheat is cooking, peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the<strong> sliced onion</strong>, <strong>shredded kale </strong>and <strong>drained lentils </strong>to the pan with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until everything has softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2228Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
